        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1076138
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-09-22T21:56:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "But this defeats the purpose of what the toolchain team needs.\n\nThe toolchain team needs a single use flag that makes every single seccomp policy on the system use SECCOMP_RET_LOG. So unless we want to change every single ebuild that uses minijail to also set the env variable, I think the sed approach is actually clearer.",
      "parentUuid": "8d3e515d_ec3bb7fe",
      "revId": "a4e5bb2bc2dcedeae5b27995e6990779f562cc46",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c1607bd3_150e5be9",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1299283
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-09-22T22:04:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The sed approach isn\u0027t fundamentally different than calling export YOUR_VAR_NAME\u003dtrue before running:\n```\n./build_packages --nousepkg ...\n```\n\nYou wouldn\u0027t need to change every single ebuild, just the cros-workon.eclass. The point would be so that portage is able to know when a package needs to be recompiled to include the different policy. Otherwise the developer has to keep track of it themselves which makes it easy to forget about binary packages that would be built with the wrong settings.",
      "parentUuid": "60a4c635_84382c0b",
      "revId": "a4e5bb2bc2dcedeae5b27995e6990779f562cc46",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
