      "writtenOn": "2021-09-23T22:51:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Are there any other ways to modify the behaviour of the python compiler by changing a single switch? This is functionality that the toolchain folks asked for: change one central setting and have everything use SECCOMP_RET_LOG.",
      "parentUuid": "3a97d62a_c3ad478c",
      "revId": "a4e5bb2bc2dcedeae5b27995e6990779f562cc46",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fce71518_3f40b6b8",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1076138
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-09-27T20:57:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Given that this is functionality is something that we promised the toolchain team, I would like to go ahead with this CL unless we have another solution that would let us make a single change at build_packages time that would ensure all policies are compiled in debug mode. Note that command-line options don\u0027t really work if we need to depend on every package using the compiler calling the command-line option.\n\nSo, unless we have a better solution, I would move forward with this approach.",
      "parentUuid": "d4bef4d7_f50b4cbd",
      "revId": "a4e5bb2bc2dcedeae5b27995e6990779f562cc46",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
